owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

collections(address).notice: Maps the collection addresses to the collection contracts

getCollectionBaseUri(address).notice: Returns the base uri of a collection

getCollectionMaxSupply(address).notice: Returns the max supply of tokens that a collection allows

getCollectionName(address).notice: Returns the name of a collection

getCollectionOwner(address).notice: Returns the owner of a collection

getCollectionSymbol(address).notice: Returns the symbol of a collection

getTokenUri(address,uint256).notice: Returns the uri of a token

mintFromCollection(address,address).notice: Mint a token from a chosen collection

ownerToCollection(address).notice: Maps the collection addresses to the contract owner addresses
